		<title>A Mouse in the Walls of the Lesser Redoubt (Part 1)</title>
		<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://nightland.website/index.php/stories/night-land-stories/the-last-redoubt/86-a-mouse-in-the-walls-of-the-lesser-redoubt/291-a-mouse-in-the-walls-of-the-lesser-redoubt-part-1"/>
		<published>2022-07-08T21:44:14+00:00</published>
		<updated>2022-07-08T21:44:14+00:00</updated>
		<id>https://nightland.website/index.php/stories/night-land-stories/the-last-redoubt/86-a-mouse-in-the-walls-of-the-lesser-redoubt/291-a-mouse-in-the-walls-of-the-lesser-redoubt-part-1</id>
		<author>
			<name>Nigel Atkinson</name>
			<email>coady.k@protonmail.com</email>
		</author>
		<summary type="html">&lt;div class=&quot;feed-description&quot;&gt;&lt;h3 class=&quot;story-teaser&quot;&gt;By &lt;a href=&quot;https://nightland.website/index.php/about/authors-and-artists/109-nigel-atkinson&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener noreferrer&quot;&gt;Nigel Atkinson&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;story-intro&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;story-thumb&quot; src=&quot;https://nightland.website/images/thumbs/fabian-lesser-redoubt-thumb.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;A traveller beholds a tall pyramid in darkness.&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In the Lesser Redoubt, when the Master Monstruwacan dies, his designated successor undergoes an ordeal before he can succeed to his office. But who does he converse with? Are the visions that he sees true showings or false? What choices does he make?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When the last candidate Master Monstruwacan of the Lesser Redoubt undergoes the ordeal — he makes a choice. But is the path he chooses painful yet necessary? Or is it a great betrayal?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;feed-readmore&quot;&gt;&lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;https://nightland.website/index.php/stories/night-land-stories/the-last-redoubt/86-a-mouse-in-the-walls-of-the-lesser-redoubt/291-a-mouse-in-the-walls-of-the-lesser-redoubt-part-1&quot;&gt;Read More ...&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</summary>
		<content type="html">&lt;div class=&quot;feed-description&quot;&gt;&lt;h3 class=&quot;story-teaser&quot;&gt;By &lt;a href=&quot;https://nightland.website/index.php/about/authors-and-artists/109-nigel-atkinson&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener noreferrer&quot;&gt;Nigel Atkinson&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;story-intro&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;story-thumb&quot; src=&quot;https://nightland.website/images/thumbs/fabian-lesser-redoubt-thumb.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;A traveller beholds a tall pyramid in darkness.&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In the Lesser Redoubt, when the Master Monstruwacan dies, his designated successor undergoes an ordeal before he can succeed to his office. But who does he converse with? Are the visions that he sees true showings or false? What choices does he make?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When the last candidate Master Monstruwacan of the Lesser Redoubt undergoes the ordeal — he makes a choice. But is the path he chooses painful yet necessary? Or is it a great betrayal?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;feed-readmore&quot;&gt;&lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;https://nightland.website/index.php/stories/night-land-stories/the-last-redoubt/86-a-mouse-in-the-walls-of-the-lesser-redoubt/291-a-mouse-in-the-walls-of-the-lesser-redoubt-part-1&quot;&gt;Read More ...&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content>
